Russian Movers: Mechel, Raspadskaya and Rosneft Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-03-17T16:39:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/russian-movers-mechel-raspadskaya-and-rosneft-are-active.html
The 30-stock Micex Index gained 1.9
percent to 1,737.62 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index added 1.6 percent to 1,945.74  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO  Raspadskaya (RASP)   increased for a second day after
three people with knowledge of the matter said on March 15 that
OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  is considering acquiring shares in the Russian coal
producer. The stock climbed 3 percent to 195.17 rubles after
adding 3.2 percent yesterday.  Mechel,  Russia ’s largest miner of steelmaking coal, added
0.9 percent to 849.9 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), Russia’s biggest oil producer,
gained by its most in three weeks, adding 1.7 percent to 256.66
rubles. Crude advanced as much as 3.1 percent as concern
political unrest may cut Middle Eastern exports countered
estimates that the earthquake in  Japan  will curtail fuel demand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran in Moscow at 
 jcorcoran13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
